An immutable utility class to sign a jar file. 
<p> A caller creates a <code>JarSigner.Builder</code> object, (optionally) sets some parameters, and calls <a href="JarSigner.Builder.html#build()"><code>build</code></a> to create a <code>JarSigner</code> object. This <code>JarSigner</code> object can then be used to sign a jar file. </p>
<p> Unless otherwise stated, calling a method of <code>JarSigner</code> or <code>JarSigner.Builder</code> with a null argument will throw a <a href="../../../../java.base/java/lang/NullPointerException.html" title="class in java.lang"><code>NullPointerException</code></a>. </p>
<p> Example: </p>
<pre> JarSigner signer = new JarSigner.Builder(key, certPath)
         .digestAlgorithm("SHA-1")
         .signatureAlgorithm("SHA1withDSA")
         .build();
 try (ZipFile in = new ZipFile(inputFile);
         FileOutputStream out = new FileOutputStream(outputFile)) {
     signer.sign(in, out);
 }
 </pre>
